Veteran Nigerian actor, Larry Williams is dead. This was announced in a statement by his family members, stating that burial arrangements will be disclosed soon. According to reports gathered, the actor died on Sunday after a prolonged illness in Ikom, Cross River State. “He will be greatly missed by his family and many friends. Burial arrangements will be announced soon,” the statement partly read. Recall that, the first president of the Actors’ Guild of Nigeria starred in different in soap operas such as Village Headmaster, Ripples, and Mirror in The Sun.